William Clay Ford Jr. - Wikipedia






















 






William Clay Ford Jr.

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from William Clay Ford, Jr.)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

"Bill Ford" redirects here. For other people of the similar name, see William Ford (disambiguation).


William Clay Ford Jr.



Ford in March 2011 speaking at the TED Conference



Born
(1957-05-03) May 3, 1957 (age 60)
Detroit, Michigan, U.S.


Nationality
American


Education
Hotchkiss School (1975)[1]
Princeton University (B.A., 1979)
MIT Sloan School of Management (S.M., 1984)


Occupation
Executive chairman, Ford Motor Company


